		"description": "{html}<div><p>There is a bug in the 1.5 build only where a gradient will cover\nup any child elements.</p>\n<p>Ticket: <a href=\n\"http://developer.appcelerator.com/helpdesk/view/55911\">http://developer.appcelerator.com/helpdesk/view/55911</a><br>\nMy Example code: <a href=\n\"http://pastie.org/1318202\">http://pastie.org/1318202</a><br>\nScreenshot: <a href=\n\"http://screencast.com/t/LoOuSFWdC0C\">http://screencast.com/t/LoOuSFWdC0C</a></p>\n<p>Also, the customer is using a radial gradient but it happens\nwith a linear gradient as well. It doesn't just happen with images\neither, here's an example of a label being masked by the gradient:\n<a href=\n\"http://screencast.com/t/Fdr8qMYH1\">http://screencast.com/t/Fdr8qMYH1</a></p></div>{html}",
